    "text": {
      "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b><a href=\"/Main_Page\" title=\"Main Page\">Home</a> * <a href=\"/People\" title=\"People\">People</a> * Mark Watson</b>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:180px;\"><a href=\"http://www.markwatson.com/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/4/46/Markws.jpg\" width=\"178\" height=\"228\" class=\"thumbimage\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/File:Markws.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Mark Watson <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></div></div></div> \n<p><b>Mark Watson</b>,<br />\nan American computer scientist, programmer, consultant and author of books on <a href=\"/Artificial_Intelligence\" title=\"Artificial Intelligence\">Artificial Intelligence</a>, <a href=\"/Java\" title=\"Java\">Java</a>, <a href=\"/index.php?title=Ruby&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Ruby (page does not exist)\">Ruby</a>, <a href=\"/index.php?title=Lisp&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Lisp (page does not exist)\">Common LISP</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Semantic_Web\">Semantic Web</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Neuro-linguistic_programming\">NLP</a>, <a href=\"/Cpp\" title=\"Cpp\">C++</a>, <a href=\"/Linux\" title=\"Linux\">Linux</a>, <a href=\"/index.php?title=Scheme&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Scheme (page does not exist)\">Scheme</a>, and <a href=\"/Windows\" title=\"Windows\">Windows</a>. \n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Go_and_Chess\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Go and Chess</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Selected_Publications\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Selected Publications</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#External_Links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External Links</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Go_and_Chess\">Go and Chess</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Mark_Watson&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Go and Chess\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p>Mark Watson is an avid Chess and <a href=\"/Go\" title=\"Go\">Go</a> player, and wrote the first commercial Go playing program, <i>Honninbo Warrior</i> for the <a href=\"/Apple_II\" title=\"Apple II\">Apple II</a> in the late 1970s <sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>. He also wrote the free <a href=\"/Basic\" title=\"Basic\">Basic</a> chess program, <a href=\"/index.php?title=Apple&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Apple (page does not exist)\">Apple</a> distributed on their Apple II demo cassette tape <sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>. <a href=\"/Mark_Watson_Chess\" title=\"Mark Watson Chess\">Mark Watson Chess</a> participated at the <a href=\"/MCCT_1978\" title=\"MCCT 1978\">Second West Coast Computer Faire Microcomputer Chess Tournament</a> in March 1978 in the class C section <sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>. His <a href=\"/Artificial_Intelligence\" title=\"Artificial Intelligence\">artificial intelligence</a> <a href=\"/Programming\" title=\"Programming\">programming</a> with <a href=\"/Java\" title=\"Java\">Java</a> textbook <sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>, accompanied with an associated <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GitHub\">GitHub</a> source code repository <sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>, comes with a Java chess program skeleton <sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> and much more AI-topics under the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Apache_License\">Apache 2.0 License</a> or under the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GNU_Lesser_General_Public_License\">GNU Lesser General Public License 3</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>. \n</p>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Selected_Publications\">Selected Publications</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Mark_Watson&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Selected Publications\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p><sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<ul><li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Mark Watson</a> (<b>1994</b>). <i>C++ Power Paradigms</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/McGraw-Hill\">McGraw-Hill</a>, from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.amazon.com/C-Power-Paradigms-Mark-Watson/dp/0079117864\">amazon</a>&#160;» <a href=\"/Cpp\" title=\"Cpp\">C++</a>, <a href=\"/Genetic_Programming#GeneticAlgorithm\" title=\"Genetic Programming\">Genetic Algorithms</a>, <a href=\"/Neural_Networks\" title=\"Neural Networks\">Neural Networks</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Mark Watson</a> (<b>2009</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.markwatson.com/books/web3_book/index.html\">Scripting Intelligence: Web 3.0 Information, Gathering and Processing</a></i>. APress 2009 </li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Mark Watson</a> (<b>2010</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.markwatson.com/books/\">Practical Semantic Web and Linked Data Applications, Java, Scala, Clojure, and JRuby Edition</a></i>. </li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Mark Watson</a> (<b>2011</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.markwatson.com/books/\">Practical Semantic Web and Linked Data Applications, Common Lisp Edition</a></i>. </li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Mark Watson</a> (<b>2013</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://leanpub.com/javaai\">Practical Artificial Intelligence Programming With Java</a></i>. Fourth Edition </li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Mark Watson</a> (<b>2017</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://leanpub.com/lovinglisp\">Loving Lisp, or the Savvy Programmer's Secret Weapon</a></i>. Fourth Edition </li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_Links\">External Links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Mark_Watson&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: External Links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.markwatson.com/\">Mark Watson: Java, Clojure, and Ruby Consultant and Author</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://plus.google.com/117612439870300277560/about\">Mark Watson - Google+</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://github.com/mark-watson?tab=repositories\">Mark Watson · GitHub</a></li></ul>\n<dl><dd> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://github.com/mark-watson/Java-AI-Book-Code/tree/master/src/search/game\">Java-AI-Book-Code/src/search/game at master · mark-watson/Java-AI-Book-Code · GitHub</a></dd></dl>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://markwatson.com/blog/\">Mark Watson's Blog</a>,</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://radio-weblogs.com/0115954/2003/03/27.html\">Mark Watson's Blog</a>, 2003</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.chessgames.com/perl/chessplayer?pid=94276\">The chess games of Mark Watson</a> from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.chessgames.com/index.html\">chessgames.com</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Mark_Watson&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.markwatson.com/\">Mark Watson: Java, Clojure, and Ruby Consultant and Author</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://radio-weblogs.com/0115954/2003/03/27.html\">Mark Watson's Blog</a>, March 27, 2003</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://blog.markwatson.com/2010/09/why-doesnt-itunes-support-ogg-sound-files-out-of-the-box/\">why doesn’t iTunes support Ogg sound files ‘out of the box’? | Mark Watson's Blog</a>, September 9, 2010</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"/Larry_Wagner\" title=\"Larry Wagner\">Larry Wagner</a> (<b>1978</b>). <i>Results of First Microcomputer Chess Tournament</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.computerhistory.org/collections/accession/102686281\">Silicon Gulch Gazette</a>, Vol. 2, No. 4, May 10, 1978, pg. 9</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Mark Watson</a> (<b>2008</b>). <i>Practical Artificial Intelligence Programming With Java</i>. Third Edition, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.markwatson.com/opencontent_data/JavaAI3rd.pdf\">pdf</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://github.com/mark-watson/Java-AI-Book-Code/tree/master/src\">Java-AI-Book-Code/src at master · mark-watson/Java-AI-Book-Code · GitHub</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-7\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://github.com/mark-watson/Java-AI-Book-Code/tree/master/src/search/game\">Java-AI-Book-Code/src/search/game at master · mark-watson/Java-AI-Book-Code · GitHub</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-8\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-8\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://github.com/mark-watson/Java-AI-Book-Code/tree/master/licenses-for-book-code\">Java-AI-Book-Code/licenses-for-book-code at master · mark-watson/Java-AI-Book-Code · GitHub</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-9\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-9\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.markwatson.com/books/\">Mark Watson's books on Java, Artificial Intelligence, Text Mining, Ruby, Common Lisp, Clojure, and C++</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<p><b><a href=\"/People\" title=\"People\">Up one level</a></b>\n</p>\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260301083027\nCache expiry: 86400\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.023 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.025 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 145/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 326/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 0/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 0/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 2/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%    0.000      1 -total\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key oscar70_mw1-mw_:pcache:idhash:3027-0!canonical and timestamp 20260301083027 and revision id 8861\n -->\n"
